args: You said it.\nWhy aren't we getting any customers?
I wonder. I suppose we'll\nhave to take drastic measures.
We'll investigate the most popular stands!\nThat way, we can figure out what they\nhave that we don't.
Right... I need to find something definitive\nto help us break out of this slump.
Let's see... Oh, that stand seems to have\nquite the line. What is it for?
Welcome to the Harmonia Choir's stand,\nHarmunchia!
We have Mariti-shaped cotton candy\nand baby Mariti-shaped ice cream!
SQUEE! Everything is just so CUTE here!\nThe sales girl, the cotton candy,\nEVERYTHING! I'll have the works, please!
Got another cotton candy coming down the\nline for you, Pia.
(How are we going to compete with such\nwholesomeness?!)
I see... So we're up against Maritimus\nand the choir kids. Tough competition.
The cuteness was overwhelming. That must\nbe what's drawing in all those customers.
At the very least, we could use a billboard\nto attract attention. With Harmunchia,\nMariti is what makes them stand out.
Maybe we can give our sign a bit more...\noomph?
There's an idea! A fancy sign should\ndefinitely drum up some business.
Our current one doesn't really pop. It's just\nthe name of our stand. Maybe if we had a\npicture of a tasty apple on it?
W-well, as it so happens, we DO have\na sign with a picture of an apple on it...
We do?! Then why aren't we using it?
Uh, it's... Well, maybe you should just\nsee for yourself.
(I knew Cleo wasn't much of an artist,\nbut this is DIRE.)
(Yikes. I can't think of anything nice to\nsay.)
Holy mackerel! Cleo, did YOU paint this?
Yes, Iâ€”wait, when did you get here,\nFleur?!
I've never seen something so freaky and\nweird! This is a blazing ghost, right?
No... It's supposed to be an apple.
We have a favor to ask of you.
That apple looks so mouthwatering, I'd be\ntempted to lick the sign if I wasn't sure\nit'd taste like dried paint.
You really are as good as they say,\nFleur. Thank you so much!
Now THIS is bound to bring some\nfolks our way.
No. This is far from enough.
Oh, Francesca! Wait... Do you not have\na stand you should be attending to?
Nope! Festivals are for schmoozing\nand making connections. I'm focusing\non building my customer base today.
But yeah, way to go, Fleur. This is a\nfantastic billboard. However, there's\none thing still missing.
Duh! A snappy catchphrase is vital!\nYou need something that'll really capture\nthe hearts of any potential customers.
True. That WOULD be good for when\nwe're trying to lure people over.
Right? Now, let's see... With your stand,\nI think we could do something like...
ï¼‚A flavor so good, it wowed the Founder\nKing himself!ï¼‚ How's that sound?
It is NOT! It is most disrespectful to use\nHis Majesty's name in such a manner!
Okay, then... How about this:\nï¼‚Candy apples your taste buds can't resist!ï¼‚
Now THERE'S a slogan. Do the\ntwo of you have any suggestions?
Hmmm... Maybe something like...\nï¼‚The flavor of loveï¼‚? Er, not that I'm\nin love or anything!
How about... ï¼‚Tubular, swell, funky-fresh,\ncosmopolitan candy apples sold hereï¼‚?
P-please, no more! I couldn't possibly\nembarrass myself like that.
Sounds like quitter talk to me. You're\ngonna NEED something with a big impact\nif you wanna make it big.
Show the people you've got something\nnobody else has. Now c'mon, keep the\nideas rolling in!
(I-I don't know how much more of this\nI can take...)
Are we really going through with this?
You bet your butt we are. Now, go!\nJakob, you're on sign duty!\nRodrigo, get advertising!

Come try the pride of Grastaea's forests!
These mouthwatering candy apples have
captivated people from all throughout
Alberia!
(I know this is to drum up attention, but...\nThis feels deceptive. I'm so embarrassed.)
(Is this really going to get us any\ncustomers...? Oh!)
People all throughout Alberia?!\nThat's a CRAZY amount of people!\nI've gotta try one of these things!
Thanks! Now for the taste test.\n*munch* Oh, geez... This is...
(I knew we couldn't possibly live up to\nthat advertisement! I can just see how\ndisappointedâ€”)
This is, like, STUPID good! Oh my GOSH,\nthey weren't kidding when they said these\nwere captivating!
Wait, seriously? Are they really that good?
They certainly look appetizing.\nCould I have two, please?
R-right away! Thank you so much!
I can't believe it. The line's suddenly\nwinding around the way. I'm shocked at\nhow much a sign and a slogan can do.
Hey, marketing is great for drawing\nattention, but it's not worth squat if the\nproduct can't live up to your promises.
The whole reason people are lining up is\nbecause YOU'RE just that good.
Put simply, you're a candy apple virtuoso!
Thank you all. After being showered with\nsuch praise, I have a lot to live up to.
I'm going to work my tail off making the\nsweetest summer treats this land has ever\nseen!
